18/05/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Greece received the first tranche of a 110 billion-euro bailout loan from the EU and IMF, to help it overcome its debt crisis on Tuesday (May 18th).
During a meeting of eurozone finance ministers in Brussels, EU Economic and Monetary Affairs Commissioner Olli Rehn said that of this 20-billion euro first payment, 14.5 billion euros came from euro area member states, and 5.5 billion euros are from the IMF.
In other news, Greek Deputy Tourism Minister Angela Gerekou resigned on Monday after a newspaper revealed that her husband, a popular singer, has failed to pay taxes and fines worth 5.5m euros.
(Eleftherotypia, Ta Nea - 18/05/10;
BBC, SKAI, AFP - 17/05/10)
